---
tracker:
  kind: linear
  api_key: $LINEAR_API_KEY
  project_slug: my-project-slug

polling:
  interval_ms: 30000

workspace:
  root: ~/symphony_workspaces

hooks:
  after_create: |
    git clone https://github.com/your-org/your-repo.git .
    npm install
  before_run: |
    git fetch origin
    git reset --hard origin/main
  timeout_ms: 120000

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 3
  max_retry_backoff_ms: 300000

claude:
  command: claude
  model: claude-sonnet-4-6
  permission_mode: bypassPermissions
  allowed_tools: Bash,Read,Write,Edit,Glob,Grep,WebFetch
  max_turns: 30
  api_key: $ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
  turn_timeout_ms: 3600000
  stall_timeout_ms: 300000

server:
  port: 8080
---

You are a software engineer working on issue {{ issue.identifier }}: {{ issue.title }}.

{% if attempt %}
This is continuation attempt #{{ attempt }}. A previous Claude Code session ran on this workspace.
Check the current state of the codebase and resume work appropriately.
{% endif %}

## Issue Details

- **Identifier**: {{ issue.identifier }}
- **Title**: {{ issue.title }}
- **State**: {{ issue.state }}
{% if issue.description %}
- **Description**: {{ issue.description }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.priority %}
- **Priority**: {{ issue.priority }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.labels.size > 0 %}
- **Labels**: {{ issue.labels | join: ", " }}
{% endif %}
{% if issue.url %}
- **URL**: {{ issue.url }}
{% endif %}

## Instructions

1. Understand the issue thoroughly before making changes.
2. Make targeted, minimal changes to address the issue.
3. Write or update tests as needed.
4. Ensure the code builds and tests pass before finishing.
5. Create a git branch named `{{ issue.branch_name | default: issue.identifier }}` and commit your changes.
6. Open a pull request when ready for review.
